         <abstract id="aspace_a80d4672a6ed7e4bda526bbdfded53ab">Writings, collected material, and glass slides document the Hales' life and work in China. Lyman and Sadie Hale were American Methodist missionaries to China from 1915 to 1941 and 1945 to 1949. They were stationed in Wuhu (1916-1925), Nanking(1925-1927, 1945-1949), Shanghai (1927-1929), and Chinkiang (1929-1941).</abstract>
